list.title: errorMessage
list.description:
If the `input` is null, undefined or an empty string, returns
'Required field'. If the `input` can be converted to a non-zero number,
returns an empty string. Otherwise, if the `input` is zero, NaN or
a non-numeric string, returns 'Must be a number besides 0'.

list.title: luckyNumber
list.description: Checks whether a number is a palindrome.

list.title: twoSum
list.description: Sums two numbers represented as arrays of digits (0-9).
